        "text": "An idea for an exercise that might be fun:\n- have a 3 hour work shop to build a little game\n- everyone starts on their own machine\n- every 15 minutes, a whistle blows and they have to get up and move to the machine on their left and continue building the game based on their neighbour's progress\n- everyone reviews the history of each project to work out why some projects proceeded faster than others\n\nMight learn a little bit about language design and readability \/ safety but more about engineering practices. I think students would quickly invent a lot of strategies for how to leave incomplete work e.g. inline documentation about what they were aiming to achieve.",
